Cell[TextData[{
 "An ",
 StyleBox["oracle",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " in computer science is a \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]black box\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] entity that is able to produce a solution for any \
instance of a given problem without revealing how the solution was obtained.  \
That being the case, the details of its implementation and its complexity are \
disregarded. Oracles are commonly used in computer science to theoretically \
classify problems in computational complexity theory, to analyze the \
complexity of algorithms, or to provide a way to solve problems. The concept \
of an oracle (i.e., black box) is a powerful tool in many other sciences as \
well that enables us to concentrate on what a device does without worrying \
about how to it is accomplished. In a decision problem, such as the \
Deutsch-Jozsa and related problems, we are supposed to figure out the unknown \
property by making queries to the oracle."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->277305066,ExpressionUUID->"4a37bf45-87b9-4b74-af4b-dfc9b5e895a6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In this document, we examine a ",
 StyleBox["quantum oracle",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", i.e., a quantum mechanical implementation of oracle."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1509494365,ExpressionUUID->"5cb9d4ff-6a3c-466a-93bf-d98675e86c9c"],

